info.headline: Flood Advisory issued July 23 at 3:05AM CDT until July 23 at 6:15AM CDT by NWS Duluth MN
info.description:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.
* WHERE...In Minnesota, Cook County.
* WHEN...Until 615 AM CDT Wednesday.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 305 AM CDT Wednesday, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the advisory area. Between 1.5 and 3 inches of rain have fallen. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Grand Marais, Lutsen, Tofte, Cascade River State Park, Eagle Mountain, Temperance River State Park, Taconite Harbor, Judge Magney State Park, Judge C. R. Magney State Park, Sugar Loaf Cove, Hovland, southeastern Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness, Elbow Lake, Caribou Lake, Cascade Lake, Two Island Lake, Tail Lake, Devil Track Lake and White Pine Lake. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction: Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.

parameter.value: FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 615 AM CDT THIS MORNING
